# Vue / Nuxt / TypeScript standards

## Structure

- Match existing patterns in the same folder (naming, Pinia stores, `$fetch` / API client)
- Prefer small focused modules over mega-files; extract helpers to `app/utils/` or `server/utils/` when reused
- Do not reintroduce removed features (e.g. Bill Entry UI) or Supabase client code

## Vue components

- `<script setup lang="ts">`; typed props/emits
- Keep template logic light — computed/composables for derived state
- Lists that open large forms/modals: async-import those children (see lean-bundle rule)
- Prefer Nuxt UI (`UButton`, `UModal`, …) over one-off CSS frameworks

## Server / API

- Auth via existing Nimble session middleware; do not add alternate auth clients
- Data access: `getPrisma()`; avoid new raw `mssql` unless extending an existing raw path
- Validate inputs; use `createError` with clear `statusMessage`
- Keep handlers thin — business logic in `server/utils/`

## TypeScript & quality

- Prefer explicit types at API/store boundaries; avoid `any` unless matching legacy shapes
- No empty `catch` — log or rethrow with context
- Do not commit secrets; use `runtimeConfig` / env (`NUXT_*`)
- Leave no dead imports, unused stores, or stub pages that pull unused routes

## Diff discipline

- Change only what the task needs; no drive-by refactors or unrelated formatting
- Do not add markdown docs unless asked
